{"kanda":6,"sarga":123,"description":"","verses":[{"v":1,"dev":"प्रतिप्रयातेकाकुत्स्थेमहेन्द्रःपाकशासनः ।अब्रवीत्परमप्रीतोराघवंप्राञ्जलिंस्थितम्","trans":"Mahendra, the tamer of demon Paka, spoke very affectionately to Rama, who stood with joined palms before Dasharatha who had returned.","words":[{"d":"काकुत्स्थे","m":"Kakuthsa, Dasharatha प्रतिप्रयाते returned"},{"d":"पाकशासनः","m":"the tamer of demon Paka"},{"d":"महेन्द्रः","m":"Mahendra"},{"d":"परमप्रीतः","m":"very affectionately"},{"d":"प्राञ्जलिम्","m":"saluting with joined palms"},{"d":"स्थितम्","m":"stood"},{"d":"राघवम्","m":"Raghava"},{"d":"अब्रवीत्","m":"spoke"}]},{"v":2,"dev":"अमोघंदर्शनंराम तवास्माकंनरर्षभ ।प्रीतियुक्ताःस्मतेनत्वंब्रूहियन्मनसेप्सितम्","trans":"\"O Rama, a bull among men! Your sight was amazing, and we are happy. Please tell us the desire in your mind?\"","words":[{"d":"नरर्षभ","m":"bull among men"},{"d":"राम","m":"Rama"},{"d":"तव","m":"your"},{"d":"अस्माकम्","m":"yourself"},{"d":"दर्शनम्","m":"sight"},{"d":"अमोघम्","m":"amazing"},{"d":"प्रीतियुक्ताः","m":"happy"},{"d":"स्म","m":"in your"},{"d":"तेन","m":"so"},{"d":"मनसा","m":"in your mind"},{"d":"यत्","m":"that which"},{"d":"ईप्सितम्","m":"desiring"},{"d":"त्वम्","m":"you"},{"d":"ब्रूहि","m":"may tell"}]},{"v":3,"dev":"एवमुक्तोमहेन्द्रेणप्रसन्नेनमहात्मना ।सुप्रसन्नमनाहृष्टोवचनंप्राहराघवः","trans":"Gratified by Mahendra's words, Raghava was very happy and pleased, submitting to him as follows.","words":[{"d":"प्रसन्नेन","m":"gratified"},{"d":"महात्मना","m":"great soul"},{"d":"महेन्द्रेण","m":"to Mahendra"},{"d":"एवम्","m":"in this way"},{"d":"उक्तः","m":"said"},{"d":"सुप्रसन्नात्मा","m":"very pleased"},{"d":"हृष्टः","m":"happy"},{"d":"वचनम्","m":"words"},{"d":"प्राह","m":"submitted"}]},{"v":4,"dev":"यदिप्रीतिस्समुत्पन्नामयितेविबुधेश्वर ।वक्ष्यामिकुरुमेसत्यंवचनंवदतांवर","trans":"\"O Lord of gods, you are one who is good at expression. If happiness has risen in, you please make my words true.\"","words":[{"d":"वदतांवर","m":"good at expression"},{"d":"विबुधेश्वर","m":"Lord of gods"},{"d":"ते","m":"you"},{"d":"मयि","m":"my"},{"d":"प्रीतिः","m":"happiness"},{"d":"समुत्पन्नायदि","m":"has risen"},{"d":"मे","m":"my"},{"d":"वचनम्","m":"words"},{"d":"सत्यम्","m":"true"},{"d":"कुरु","m":"make it"}]},{"v":5,"dev":"ममहेतोःपराक्रान्तायेगतायमसादनम् ।तेसर्वेजीवितंप्राप्यसमुततिष्ठन्तुवानराः","trans":"\"The Vanaras have fought for my cause and reached the abode of Yama. Make them rise up and get them back to life.\"","words":[{"d":"ममहेतोः","m":"for my cause"},{"d":"पराक्रान्ताः","m":"who fought"},{"d":"ये","m":"those"},{"d":"वानराः","m":"Vanaras"},{"d":"यमसादनम्","m":"abode of Yama"},{"d":"गताः","m":"reached"},{"d":"तेसर्वे","m":"all of them"},{"d":"जीवितम्","m":"life"},{"d":"प्राप्य","m":"get back"},{"d":"समुततिष्ठन्तु","m":"make them rise up"}]},{"v":6,"dev":"मत्कृतेविप्रयुक्तायेपुत्रैर्दारैश्चवानराः ।तान्प्रीतमनसःसर्वान्द्रष्टुमिच्छामिमानद","trans":"\"O honourable Indra! I wish to see all those Vanaras who are separated forever from their sons, and wives for my cause, delighted.\"","words":[{"d":"मानद","m":"honourable"},{"d":"मत्कृते","m":"for my sake"},{"d":"ये","m":"they"},{"d":"वानराः","m":"Vanaras"},{"d":"पुत्रैः","m":"sons"},{"d":"दारैश्च","m":"wives"},{"d":"विप्रयुक्ताः","m":"seperated for good"},{"d":"तान्","m":"them"},{"d":"सर्वान्","m":"all"},{"d":"प्रीतमनसः","m":"delighted"},{"d":"द्रष्टुम्","m":"to see"},{"d":"इच्छामि","m":"I wish"}]},{"v":7,"dev":"विक्रान्ताश्चापिशूराश्च न मृत्युंगणयन्ति च ।कृतयत्नाविपन्नाश्चजीवयैनान् पुरन्दर","trans":"\"They were valiant and courageous and did not care for life. They did their utmost, died and fell into adversity. Purandara! Get all of them back to life.\"","words":[{"d":"विक्रान्ताः च","m":"valiant"},{"d":"शूराश्च","m":"courageous"},{"d":"मृत्युम्","m":"death"},{"d":"न गणयन्ति च","m":"not cared for"},{"d":"कृतयत्नाः","m":"did utmost"},{"d":"विपन्नाःच","m":"fallen into adversity"},{"d":"पुरन्दर","m":"Purandara, destroyer of citadels"},{"d":"एतान्","m":"all of them"},{"d":"जीवय","m":"bring to life"}]},{"v":8,"dev":"मत्प्रियेष्वभिरक्ताश्च न मृत्युंगणयन्तिये ।त्वत्प्रसादात्समेयुस्तेवरमेतमहंवृणे","trans":"\"They were fond of doing and not counted death. I seek your grace to give a boon to relieve all of them from death.\"","words":[{"d":"मत्प्रियेषु","m":"at death"},{"d":"अभिरक्ताः","m":"fond of doing"},{"d":"ये","m":"they"},{"d":"मृत्युम्","m":"death"},{"d":"न गणयन्ति","m":"not counted"},{"d":"ते","m":"they"},{"d":"त्वत्प्रासादात्","m":"by your grace"},{"d":"समेयुः","m":"in war"},{"d":"अहम्","m":"I"},{"d":"एतम्","m":"all of them"},{"d":"वरम्","m":"boon"},{"d":"वृणे","m":"seek"}]},{"v":9,"dev":"नीरुजोनिर्व्रणांश्चैवसम्पन्नबलपौरुषान् ।गोलाङ्गूलांस्तथैवर्क्षांन्द्रष्टुमिच्छामिमानद","trans":"\"Bestower of honour! I wish to see the longtailed Vanaras, and Bears rid of pain and death, enriched with strength and courage.\"","words":[{"d":"मानद","m":"bestower of honour"},{"d":"गोलाङ्गूलान्","m":"longtailed monkeys"},{"d":"तथा","m":"similarly"},{"d":"वक्षांश्च","m":"Bears"},{"d":"नीरुजः","m":"purified without any pain"},{"d":"निर्व्रणांश्चैव","m":"from death"},{"d":"सम्पन्नबलपौरुषान्","m":"enriched with strength and courage"},{"d":"द्रष्टुम्","m":"to see"},{"d":"इच्छामि","m":"desire"}]},{"v":10,"dev":"अकालेचापिपुष्पाणिमूलानि च फलानि च ।नद्यश्चविमलास्तत्रतिष्ठेयुर्यत्रवानराः","trans":"\"Let the location where Vanaras lived, have flowers, roots, fruits even though out of season and rivers with pure water.\"","words":[{"d":"वानराः","m":"Vanaras"},{"d":"यत्र","m":"there"},{"d":"तिष्ठेयुः","m":"living"},{"d":"तत्र","m":"there"},{"d":"अकालेचापि","m":"even though out of season"},{"d":"पुष्पाणि","m":"flowers"},{"d":"मूलानि च","m":"and roots"},{"d":"फलानि च","m":"fruits"},{"d":"विमलाः","m":"pure"},{"d":"नद्यश्च","m":"rivers"}]},{"v":11,"dev":"श्रुत्वातुवचनंतस्यराघवस्यमहात्मनः ।महेन्द्रःप्रत्युवाचेदंवचनंप्रीतिसंयुतम्","trans":"Hearing high souled Raghava's words, Mahendra in turn replied as follows.","words":[{"d":"महात्मनः","m":"great self"},{"d":"तस्य","m":"his"},{"d":"राघवस्य","m":"Raghava's"},{"d":"वचनम्","m":"words"},{"d":"श्रुत्वातु","m":"hearing also"},{"d":"महेन्द्रः","m":"Mahendra"},{"d":"प्रीतिसंयुतम्","m":"replied"},{"d":"इदम्","m":"this"},{"d":"वचनम्","m":"words"},{"d":"प्रत्युवाच","m":"in turn"}]},{"v":12,"dev":"महानयंवरस्तातयस्त्वयोक्तोरघूत्तम ।वदिर्मयानोक्तपूर्वं च तस्मादेतद्भविष्यति","trans":"\"Dear Rama! that which has been sought by you is great. Nothing has been revised by me in the past. Therefore, everything asked by you will be granted by this boon.\"","words":[{"d":"तात","m":"dear"},{"d":"रघूत्तम","m":"foremost of Raghus"},{"d":"यः","m":"that which"},{"d":"त्वया","m":"by you"},{"d":"उक्तः","m":"sought"},{"d":"अयम्","m":"this"},{"d":"वरः","m":"boon"},{"d":"महान्","m":"great"},{"d":"मया","m":"by me"},{"d":"वदिः","m":"asked"},{"d":"न उक्तपूर्वम्","m":"even before you asked"},{"d":"तस्मात्","m":"therefore"},{"d":"एतत्","m":"everything"},{"d":"एवम्","m":"in that way"},{"d":"भविष्यति","m":"will be granted"}]},{"v":13,"dev":"समुत्तिष्ठन्तुतेसर्वेहतायेयुधिराक्षसैः ।ऋक्षाश्चसहगोपुच्छैर्निकृत्ताननबाहवः","trans":"\"Let those long tailed Vanaras and Bears killed by Rakshasas, whose heads and arms had been severed, duly rise to life.\"","words":[{"d":"ये","m":"those"},{"d":"युधि","m":"combat"},{"d":"राक्षसैः","m":"by the Rakshasas"},{"d":"हताः","m":"killed"},{"d":"तेसर्वे","m":"all of them"},{"d":"निकृत्ताननबाहवः","m":"severed arms and heads deformed"},{"d":"गोपुच्छैः","m":"long tailed"},{"d":"ऋक्षाश्च","m":"Bears"},{"d":"समुत्तिष्ठन्तु","m":"duly rise to life"}]},{"v":14,"dev":"नीरुजोनिर्व्रणाश्चैवसम्पन्नबलपौरुषाः ।समुत्थास्यन्तिहरयस्सुप्तानिद्राक्ष्येयथा","trans":"The monkeys duly healed, so also from death, enriched with strength and power rose up like rising from sleep.","words":[{"d":"हरयः","m":"monkeys"},{"d":"नीरुजः","m":"healed"},{"d":"निर्व्रणाश्चैव","m":"from death"},{"d":"सम्पन्नबलपौरुषाः","m":"enriched with strength and power"},{"d":"सुप्ताः","m":"sleeping"},{"d":"निद्राक्ष्येयथा","m":"like rising from sleep"},{"d":"समुत्थास्यन्ति","m":"rise up"}]},{"v":15,"dev":"सुहृद्भिर्बान्धवैश्चैवज्ञातिभिःस्वजनेन च ।सर्वएवसमेष्यन्तिसम्युक्ताःपरयामुदा","trans":"\"Let all in that way happily get reunited and highly rejoiced, with relatives, own clan and own people get united.\"","words":[{"d":"सर्वेएव","m":"all in that way"},{"d":"मुदा","m":"happily"},{"d":"सम्युक्ताः","m":"reunited"},{"d":"सुहृद्भिः","m":"highly rejoiced"},{"d":"बान्धवैश्चैव","m":"with relatives"},{"d":"ज्ञातिभिः","m":"own clan"},{"d":"स्वजनेन","m":"own people"},{"d":"समेष्यन्ति","m":"will get united"}]},{"v":16,"dev":"अकालेपुष्पशबलाःफलवन्तश्चपादपाः ।भविष्यन्तिमहेष्वास नद्यश्चसलिलायुताः","trans":"The trees will be with blossoms and fruits even though it is unseasonal. The rivers will remain with waters.","words":[{"d":"महेष्वास","m":"wielder of great bow"},{"d":"पादपाः","m":"trees"},{"d":"अकाले","m":"unseason"},{"d":"पुष्पशबलाः","m":"with blossom"},{"d":"फलवन्तश्च","m":"and with fruits"},{"d":"भविष्यन्ति","m":"will be"},{"d":"नद्यश्च","m":"rivers"},{"d":"सलिलायुताः","m":"remain with water"}]},{"v":17,"dev":"सव्रणैःप्रथमंगात्रैरिदानींनिर्व्रणैस्समैः ।ततस्समुत्थितास्सर्वेसुप्त्वेवहरियूथपाः बभूवुर्वानरास्सर्वेकिंन्वेतदितिविस्मिताः ।","trans":"All the army of Vanaras healed from the wounds, who were earlier covered with wounds and all the dead monkeys together rose up like getting up from sleep. They were amazed and started saying 'What happened'!","words":[{"d":"ततः","m":"then"},{"d":"सर्वे","m":"all"},{"d":"हरियूथपाः","m":"army of Vanaras"},{"d":"प्रथमम्","m":"earlier"},{"d":"सव्रणैः","m":"of the wounds"},{"d":"इदानीम्","m":"these"},{"d":"निर्व्रणैः","m":"dead"},{"d":"समैः","m":"united"},{"d":"गात्रैः","m":"limbs"},{"d":"सुप्त्वेव","m":"having slept"},{"d":"समुथतिताः","m":"like getting up"},{"d":"सर्वे","m":"all"},{"d":"वानराः","m":"Vanaras"},{"d":"एतत्","m":"these"},{"d":"किंनु","m":"What happened"},{"d":"इति","m":"this"},{"d":"विस्मिताः","m":"amazed"},{"d":"बभूवुः","m":"became"}]},{"v":18,"dev":